articles.description: Robert Johnson scored a career-high 29 points on nine 3s and Indiana rallied from an early 13-point deficit and then held off Iowa 84-82, picking up its fourth straight victory.
articles.headline: Indiana rallies, holds off Iowa 84-82

articles.description: Ronald Delph scored a career-high 24 points, Justin Massey added 18 with four 3-pointers, and FAU rallied to beat FIU 77-72 on Saturday to end a four-game skid and split the season series with the Golden Panthers.
articles.headline: Delph's career day lifts FAU over FIU 77-72

articles.description: Devontavius Payne scored 22 points and East Tennessee State bounced back after having its 16-game winning streak snapped with a 72-61 win over Western Carolina on Saturday.
articles.headline: Payne has 22, ETSU bounces back, tops W Carolina 72-61

articles.description: Kentucky's Quade Green delivers a pass to a cutting Jarred Vanderbilt for a two-handed flush.
articles.headline: Vanderbilt gets behind defense for dunk

images.caption: Kentucky's Quade Green delivers a pass to a cutting Jarred Vanderbilt for a two-handed flush.
images.name: Vanderbilt gets behind defense for dunk

articles.description: Michigan State comes roaring back in the second half and ties the game at 53 after Nick Ward's putback.
articles.headline: Spartans tie it on Ward's putback

articles.description: Jaren Jackson Jr. gets the ball in the low post and scores from there to give the Spartans their first lead over Northwestern at 55-53.
